Rowland Alston (7 June 1782 – 21 November 1865) was an English politician.
He was a Member of Parliament (MP) for Hertfordshire from 1835 to 1841. He lived at Pishiobury, Sawbridgeworth, Hertfordshire.

response: Later residents include Rowland Alston (1782–1865), the brewer Francis Charrington and Francis William Buxton (1847–1911), barrister and Liberal Party politician.
*Sir Rowland Alston, 2nd Baronet (c.1654–1697) of the Alston Baronets
*Sir Rowland Alston, 4th Baronet (c.1678–1769) MP for Bedfordshire 1722-1741
*Sir Rowland Alston, 6th Baronet (died 1791), High Sheriff of Bedfordshire
